1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,900
[Manito means a secret friend.]

2
00:00:01,900 --> 00:00:05,500
[In this novel gathering
where each member is assigned a gift recipient
through methods such as draws,]

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:08,540
[they must deliver a gift or an act of kindness
without being discovered.]

4
00:00:15,620 --> 00:00:18,680
In this era where laughter and warmth
are diminishing,

5
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:24,070
there is a group of people who go undercover
with the aim to change the world.

6
00:00:26,150 --> 00:00:28,180
In the name of Santa Claus,

7
00:00:28,290 --> 00:00:32,180
Genie, and Snail Bride,
they deliver unexpected gifts.

8
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:35,560
They belong to the same organization.

9
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:39,150
That is the Manito Club.

10
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:40,960
A gathering of people

11
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:44,330
who know that
happiness doubles when shared.

12
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:47,640
There's only one rule...

13
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:51,030
[Remain anonymous.]

14
00:00:51,740 --> 00:00:54,750
Even at this moment, in someone's day,

15
00:00:54,870 --> 00:00:58,850
they appear and disappear like a little gift.

16
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:02,860
Manito is everywhere.

17
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:08,420
[Welcome to the Manito Club]

18
00:01:08,420 --> 00:01:11,210
Welcome to "The Secret Friends Club."

19
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:18,970
From now on,
the Manito Club is back in action.

20
00:01:22,420 --> 00:01:24,650
[Summoned to the Manito Club headquarters]

21
00:01:25,090 --> 00:01:27,980
[5 club members]

22
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:28,760
Can you tell who I am dressed like this?

23
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,180
[In disguise]

24
00:01:30,180 --> 00:01:32,729
So our identities can't be exposed.

25
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:34,250
[Delivering gifts to each other]

26
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:35,440
Run! Run!

27
00:01:35,740 --> 00:01:36,979
Who are you?

28
00:01:37,150 --> 00:01:37,470
Who are you!

29
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:38,780
[Become a regular member of Manito Club!]

30
00:01:38,780 --> 00:01:41,140
Wow! There's someone here!

31
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:44,350
[I got a gift!]

32
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:44,770
I got a gift.

33
00:01:44,770 --> 00:01:48,820
[Special privileges of Manito Club members]

34
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:49,560
I think I like receiving more than giving.

35
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:55,210
[Learning the joy of gifting and receiving gifts]

36
00:01:55,759 --> 00:01:57,070
[Last challenge to become a regular member]

37
00:01:57,070 --> 00:01:58,130
Now, what is this?

38
00:01:58,270 --> 00:01:59,880
Your next mission is Secret Manito.

39
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:01,580
[Operation Secret Manito]

40
00:02:01,770 --> 00:02:02,260
[Undercover upgrade]
[Coming soon: Secret Manitos unite]

41
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:05,710
How did such a gathering come about?

42
00:02:06,270 --> 00:02:08,530
[Welcome to "The Secret Friends Club."]

43
00:02:08,860 --> 00:02:12,510
[December 2025, Korea]
[Finding out their Manito]

44
00:02:12,770 --> 00:02:15,930
[Please let me go buy a gift ASAP.]

45
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:18,850
[Yongsan District, OA Office]

46
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:19,060
Hello.

47
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:21,510
[Jennie: Manito Club Member]

48
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,579
[This is my Manito, Kuma.]

49
00:02:23,579 --> 00:02:23,860
Ay, so cute.

50
00:02:23,860 --> 00:02:26,170
[Kuma: Jennie's pet dog]

51
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,740
[Are you OK? Are you nervous?]

52
00:02:28,790 --> 00:02:29,900
It's angry.

53
00:02:30,210 --> 00:02:30,350
[Grrr]

54
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:32,510
Oh, it's angry!

55
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,220
[Jennie: It's like
my company's (Oddatelier) mascot.]

56
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:38,800
[Jennie: It's in the office more than I am.]

57
00:02:39,050 --> 00:02:41,180
[(Grrr) Kuma, the office's guardian]

58
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:42,880
Be good.

59
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,900
[Jennie: When can I know (my Manito)?
Do you tell me now?]

60
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,810
[Jennie: Who's my Manito...]

61
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:53,650
[Jennie: If they live nearby,
I might run into them when buying gifts.]

62
00:02:53,970 --> 00:02:55,860
[She's already into the character]

63
00:02:58,590 --> 00:03:02,390
[You've been invited to the Manito Club.]

64
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:08,000
[It's a gathering of people who know that
happiness doubles when shared.]

65
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:12,560
[If you're interested, please click the link below!
https://The.Secret.Friends.Club]

66
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,430
[Yes, I am!]

67
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:21,579
[Meeting Room of Manito HQ]
[In a while, you will select your Manito
through an anonymous live draw.]

68
00:03:21,579 --> 00:03:22,740
[Panda has entered the room]

69
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:24,520
Wow! What is this? So fun.

70
00:03:25,530 --> 00:03:26,320
[Jennie's code name: Panda]

71
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:28,190
What is this? So fun.

72
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:33,550
[Manito Draw: animal mode to remain anonymous]

73
00:03:33,550 --> 00:03:34,470
[Panda] [Raccoon Dog has entered the room]

74
00:03:34,470 --> 00:03:36,610
Someone else joined! Raccoon Dog.

75
00:03:36,970 --> 00:03:38,230
Hello. Good morning.

76
00:03:38,230 --> 00:03:40,660
[Code name: Raccoon Dog]

77
00:03:40,660 --> 00:03:40,800
[Lee Sooji's code name: Raccoon Dog]

78
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,060
I'm Raccoon Dog.

79
00:03:43,190 --> 00:03:43,610
I can't show my face. OK.

80
00:03:43,610 --> 00:03:45,640
[Lee Sooji responds to the invitation in the midst
of a meeting for her YouTube content]
[(SUB) Soft Girl Ttooji's YouTube Meeting VLOG]

81
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:48,050
It only recognizes movements, like this.

82
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:51,150
[What? Am I a horse?]

83
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:51,990
[Bull has entered the room]
[Panda] [Raccoon Dog]

84
00:03:51,990 --> 00:03:53,320
Hello.

85
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,320
[Eh?]

86
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:56,360
Am I a horse or a cow?

87
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,520
[Dex's code name: Bull]

88
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,680
A bull!

89
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:04,430
[Bull is mischievous right from the get-go]

90
00:04:04,610 --> 00:04:06,680
[Bull's mouth is so cute!]

91
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:10,390
[Me too. Ah!]

92
00:04:10,610 --> 00:04:12,840
[Raccoon Dog] [Fox has entered the room]
[Panda] [Bull]

93
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:13,620
Oh, my!

94
00:04:13,780 --> 00:04:15,740
Fox has joined too.

95
00:04:15,940 --> 00:04:17,440
[Code name: Fox]

96
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:17,690
Is this sensor recognizing my movements?

97
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:20,310
[Noh Hongchul's code name: Fox]

98
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:25,750
[Bull: Wa, wa, wa, wa, wo, wo, wo, wo.]

99
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:25,860
Blink, blink.

100
00:04:25,860 --> 00:04:28,740
[Bull-style welcome greeting]

101
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:30,610
[Dex having fun like an eight-year-old kid]

102
00:04:30,610 --> 00:04:32,750
This is way too cute.

103
00:04:33,290 --> 00:04:36,710
[Muted, Raccoon Dog is fully adjusted
to the undercover animal mode]

104
00:04:36,710 --> 00:04:40,100
[Wiggling]
[Muted, Panda is fully adjusted
to the undercover animal mode]

105
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:43,500
[Fox is doing the skeleton dance]

106
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:46,250
[Rabbit has entered the room] [Fox]
[Bull] [Panda] [Raccoon Dog]

107
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:49,010
[Rabbit is frozen]

108
00:04:49,010 --> 00:04:53,970
[Choo Sunghoon's code name: Rabbit]

109
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:58,890
[Rabbit: What is this?]

110
00:04:58,890 --> 00:05:00,900
[Rabbit: What do I do…]

111
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:01,490
[Rabbit]

112
00:05:01,490 --> 00:05:02,780
[Rabbit: How...]

113
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:07,430
[Rabbit: Is this... Has it started?]

114
00:05:07,430 --> 00:05:08,090
How does this work?

115
00:05:08,090 --> 00:05:12,800
[A middle-aged man
unfamiliar with the digital world]

116
00:05:15,210 --> 00:05:15,940
[Collapses]

117
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,910
[(Weak)]

118
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:22,430
[Rabbit (Static)] [Fox] [Bull (babbles)]
[Panda]
[Raccoon Dog (sticking tongue out)]

119
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:24,310
[Rabbit (Static)] [Fox] [Bull (babbles)]
[Panda (shaking head)]
[Raccoon Dog (sticking tongue out)]

120
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:27,830
[What is this… Who are all these animals?]

121
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:29,310
[Panda: Hello!]

122
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:30,260
[Bull: Hello~]

123
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:31,530
[Fox: This will be fun^^]

124
00:05:31,530 --> 00:05:32,790
[Raccoon Dog: Hihi]

125
00:05:33,990 --> 00:05:35,740
[Someone typed "Hello."]

126
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:37,140
[I see it.]

127
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:37,850
[Chat of Meeting Room of Manito HQ]
[Panda: Hello!]

128
00:05:37,850 --> 00:05:38,560
[Chat of Meeting Room of Manito HQ]
[Bull: Hello~]

129
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,270
[Chat of Meeting Room of Manito HQ]
[Fox: This will be fun^^]

130
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:39,980
[Chat of Meeting Room of Manito HQ]
[Raccoon Dog: Hihi]

131
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:42,920
[Where do I type hello?]

132
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:45,540
[Hold on...]

133
00:05:45,540 --> 00:05:48,590
[Relentlessly pressing the innocent Num Lock key…]

134
00:05:48,860 --> 00:05:51,760
[Jennie (Panda):
Rabbit has joined the room for a while,]

135
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,670
[Jennie (Panda): but they haven't said hello yet.]

136
00:05:53,670 --> 00:05:56,300
[I don't think he's my age.]

137
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:56,570
He must be lost.

138
00:05:56,570 --> 00:05:59,020
[Somewhat pitiful Rabbit]

139
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:01,640
[Maybe (Rabbit) isn't that tech-savvy.]

140
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:05,470
[Gosh, I don't understand the computer.]

141
00:06:05,470 --> 00:06:05,780
Darn it, seriously.

142
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:09,110
[Shabby computer skills exposed right away]

143
00:06:10,190 --> 00:06:11,990
[Raccoon Dog: Has everyone eaten?]

144
00:06:13,580 --> 00:06:16,830
[Lee Sooji (Raccoon Dog): I asked
if they've eaten, but no one replied.]

145
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:17,280
What is this?

146
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:22,210
[H... H... H... Ha... Ha... Has... every...]

147
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,910
[After a tech barrier, comes a language barrier]

148
00:06:24,910 --> 00:06:27,230
Are they asking if we've eaten?

149
00:06:27,340 --> 00:06:28,930
[Food…?]

150
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:31,240
[Take care of your meals yourself.]

151
00:06:31,510 --> 00:06:33,330
[Should I send a message here?]

152
00:06:33,330 --> 00:06:34,800
[What (sniffs) should I do?]

153
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:34,990
I…

154
00:06:34,990 --> 00:06:37,360
[At a loss]

155
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:37,720
I…

156
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:40,010
[An uncle pressing everything he sees]

157
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:40,390
The mic is muted. Should I turn the mic on?

158
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:43,380
[Rabbit (unmuted)]

159
00:06:43,730 --> 00:06:46,240
[Rabbit (unmuted): Should I turn the mic on?]
[Fox + Bull + Panda + Raccoon Dog (!)]

160
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:47,010
[Big accident]

161
00:06:47,010 --> 00:06:49,370
Should I turn the mic on?

162
00:06:49,370 --> 00:06:49,890
[One member who doesn't know to go undercover]

163
00:06:49,890 --> 00:06:52,409
Should I turn the mic on?

164
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,610
-It should be off. -Oh, really?

165
00:06:54,670 --> 00:06:54,909
-You should stay muted. -Oh no. This is bad.

166
00:06:54,909 --> 00:06:55,530
[Uh…]

167
00:06:55,530 --> 00:06:57,350
[What…?]

168
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:59,760
-You should stay muted. -Oh no. This is bad.

169
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,860
[Reading the room]

170
00:07:01,210 --> 00:07:03,750
[Should we pretend we didn't hear that…?]

171
00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:04,790
[Producer… is this OK?]

172
00:07:04,790 --> 00:07:07,140
I think I should send something.

173
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:08,900
[(Panics) (Urgent)]

174
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:10,130
[Staff: This is a broadcast mishap, right?]

175
00:07:10,340 --> 00:07:11,600
[(Voice of) a middle-aged man.]

176
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:11,850
I can hear his voice directly.

177
00:07:11,850 --> 00:07:12,970
[Rabbit's identity is at risk of being exposed
right from the start]

178
00:07:12,970 --> 00:07:14,770
There's a clueless person here.

179
00:07:15,020 --> 00:07:17,240
[Wait, wait, I don't want to hear it!]

180
00:07:17,690 --> 00:07:17,840
A mishap!

181
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:20,920
[No spoilers!!!]

182
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,530
[Blah, blah, blah, blah.]

183
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,690
Hold on, that voice sounds familiar.

184
00:07:25,690 --> 00:07:27,260
[Deducing]

185
00:07:27,460 --> 00:07:27,530
He sounds a bit older.

186
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:30,340
[Vibes of a senior with much life experience]

187
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:31,610
[I know who!]

188
00:07:31,850 --> 00:07:33,090
[I really know!]

189
00:07:33,090 --> 00:07:33,950
Who is it?

190
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:34,300
Did I just catch a loophole in the production?

191
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:36,610
[Feeling smug as the production team panics]

192
00:07:36,610 --> 00:07:38,940
-OMG! -Something came out of this mishap.

193
00:07:39,470 --> 00:07:40,760
My hair…

194
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,080
[That uncle!]

195
00:07:42,390 --> 00:07:44,260
[A middle-aged man
mumbling with a deep, low voice…]

196
00:07:44,270 --> 00:07:44,480
Yes, that one. Oh.

197
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:47,320
[Mumbling]

198
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:49,040
[He was on "You Quiz."]

199
00:07:49,290 --> 00:07:51,150
[The search is narrowing down]
[Choo Sunghoon on You Quiz: "Don't underestimate
middle-aged men. I want to bring hope to them."]

200
00:07:51,150 --> 00:07:52,380
Whatever.

201
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,790
[A shy man with a husky voice.]

202
00:07:54,790 --> 00:07:55,170
Really? I…

203
00:07:55,170 --> 00:07:57,780
[A classic husky voice]

204
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:58,680
[Is it Um Taegoo?]

205
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:00,100
Huh? What?

206
00:08:00,220 --> 00:08:01,080
Is it Um Taegoo?

207
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:01,940
[Full of confidence]

208
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:03,230
Right? That's his voice.

209
00:08:03,230 --> 00:08:03,510
I'm not quite at that level yet.

210
00:08:03,510 --> 00:08:06,760
[Fortunately, she's way off the mark]

211
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:07,020
Right? It's his voice.

212
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:08,630
[Phew, what a relief]

213
00:08:10,150 --> 00:08:13,740
[A staff member rushes to mute his mic]

214
00:08:14,090 --> 00:08:15,920
[Dex (Bull): But I don't have a clue who it is.]

215
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:17,890
[I don't know which animal it was.]

216
00:08:18,190 --> 00:08:18,200
That clueless Bull.

217
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,630
[(Mistakes it as Bull)]

218
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:23,040
[Hovering around the "Leave Meeting Room" button]

219
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,770
[There's a button for leaving.]

220
00:08:24,930 --> 00:08:25,160
There's a button for leaving.

221
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:28,210
["Leave"... the easiest button
to understand on this screen…]

222
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:29,440
Should I just try leaving the room?

223
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,410
[This is confusing. Should I just leave?]

224
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:32,360
Seriously…

225
00:08:32,539 --> 00:08:32,720
Welcome, everyone.

226
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,929
[The Secret Friends Club]
[Proceeding quickly before he makes more mistakes]

227
00:08:34,929 --> 00:08:34,970
[Fox, Rabbit, Panda, Raccoon Dog, Bull]

228
00:08:34,970 --> 00:08:40,740
It's time to pick the Manito
who will receive your gift.

229
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,880
We'll do this randomly with a capsule toy machine.

230
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:45,930
Capsule toy machine.

231
00:08:45,930 --> 00:08:47,400
We'll go by numbers: #1 gives a gift to #2,

232
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:50,310
[The most cutting-edge dashboard system]

233
00:08:50,310 --> 00:08:53,410
#2 to #3, #3 to #4,

234
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:56,770
#4 to #5, and #5 to #1.

235
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:57,860
Yes.

236
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:58,740
We'll randomly draw
which animal corresponds to each number.

237
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:02,530
[The animal with the number after yours
will be your Manito!]

238
00:09:02,530 --> 00:09:03,320
OK.

239
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:05,470
[So curious!]

240
00:09:05,470 --> 00:09:07,450
[So curious!]

241
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:11,320
[Dex (Bull): The last time (I did the Manito game)
was in elementary school, I think.]

242
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:11,530
Such a game... Manito!

243
00:09:11,530 --> 00:09:14,790
[Pure dopamine rush returns after 20 odd years]

244
00:09:14,850 --> 00:09:16,420
The animal in #1 is...

245
00:09:16,540 --> 00:09:16,550
The animal in #1 is...

246
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:19,190
[Dopamine explosion!]

247
00:09:20,610 --> 00:09:21,890
Oh, like this.

248
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:23,090
[Oops.]

249
00:09:23,090 --> 00:09:25,020
[Oops, they dropped the coin...]

250
00:09:25,470 --> 00:09:25,810
[Clumsy with the capsule toy machine
on the first go]

251
00:09:25,810 --> 00:09:27,120
Oh dear.

252
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,660
[(Picking it up)]

253
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:34,650
[Inserting the coin carefully:
