00:35:57,890 --> 00:35:58,300
The special benefit is mine.

1013
00:35:58,300 --> 00:36:00,390
[The first gifter is me]

1014
00:36:00,530 --> 00:36:00,700
Because I already have two gifts.

1015
00:36:00,700 --> 00:36:02,950
[I already have two gifts]

1016
00:36:02,950 --> 00:36:03,130
[Gift 1: Vitamins]
[Gift 2: Biscuit with names]

1017
00:36:03,130 --> 00:36:04,930
I also bought the name biscuits.

1018
00:36:05,380 --> 00:36:08,450
[Jennie: Someone is enjoying
his pork cutlet right now.]

1019
00:36:08,450 --> 00:36:10,010
But I’m on the run, doing my best.

1020
00:36:10,010 --> 00:36:14,500
[Pedal to the metal
to be the first gifter!]

1021
00:36:16,590 --> 00:36:16,820
A special benefit for the first gifter.

1022
00:36:16,820 --> 00:36:21,670
[Dex, who only just noticed the HQ message]

1023
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:26,370
[Benefit for the first gifter...?]

1024
00:36:26,890 --> 00:36:29,330
[Enjoy your meal.]

1025
00:36:29,660 --> 00:36:31,590
[I'm going to buy a gift.]

1026
00:36:31,820 --> 00:36:33,380
[The crew 2: He said he was going to buy a gift?]
[The crew 1: Where did he go?]

1027
00:36:33,380 --> 00:36:34,530
[The crew 2: He said he was going to buy a gift????]
[The crew 1: To buy a gift?]

1028
00:36:34,990 --> 00:36:35,050
[Strarts running in the middle of a meal]

1029
00:36:35,050 --> 00:36:36,650
3 minutes, 3 minutes.

1030
00:36:38,350 --> 00:36:40,890
[Acting at the timing that no one expected!]

1031
00:36:41,460 --> 00:36:44,220
[Dex: The first person to give
the gift has the benefit.]

1032
00:36:44,510 --> 00:36:45,320
[The HQ's message invoked
UDT’s desire to win]

1033
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:46,890
I have to hurry.

1034
00:36:48,300 --> 00:36:48,740
[First gift Operation Area:
Convenience Store]

1035
00:36:48,740 --> 00:36:50,070
Hello.

1036
00:36:54,190 --> 00:36:57,120
[Dex: I want to buy protein drinks.]

1037
00:36:57,700 --> 00:37:00,550
[Dex: I don't know what he likes.
There are all kinds of flavors.]

1038
00:37:03,230 --> 00:37:03,430
Thank you.

1039
00:37:03,430 --> 00:37:06,410
[Got the first gift quickly]

1040
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:08,110
[What are you doing out here?]

1041
00:37:09,790 --> 00:37:12,730
[The first gift, revealed]

1042
00:37:12,770 --> 00:37:14,220
All kinds of protein shake.

1043
00:37:14,220 --> 00:37:15,930
[The first supplement]

1044
00:37:15,930 --> 00:37:18,160
I think he’ll like this gift very much.

1045
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:22,420
[Dex: Let me briefly introduce the flavors.]

1046
00:37:24,200 --> 00:37:24,240
The grams of protein included are labelled.

1047
00:37:24,240 --> 00:37:26,570
[Supplements Report]

1048
00:37:26,900 --> 00:37:28,850
[This has 43 grams.]

1049
00:37:28,850 --> 00:37:28,910
This

1050
00:37:28,910 --> 00:37:30,170
[Dex: is considered really high.]

1051
00:37:30,170 --> 00:37:33,090
[Dex: So I prepared shakes with different
grams of protein in them.]

1052
00:37:33,090 --> 00:37:33,430
20, 21, 24, 40, and 43 grams.

1053
00:37:33,430 --> 00:37:37,040
[The protein drinks prepared for exercise]

1054
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:38,500
For various preferences.

1055
00:37:38,620 --> 00:37:39,240
[Laughing]

1056
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:40,070
What?

1057
00:37:40,490 --> 00:37:41,790
[Dex: He will like it, right?]

1058
00:37:42,050 --> 00:37:43,890
[Dex: I was struggling just now.]

1059
00:37:44,480 --> 00:37:46,870
[I was wondering if I should give him
something expensive and good.]

1060
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:49,640
[Dex: But here's the thing about gifts.]

1061
00:37:50,080 --> 00:37:52,810
[Dex: It begins from the moment I think
about the gift.]

1062
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:53,620
Starting from when I think about
what to give him,

1063
00:37:53,620 --> 00:37:54,710
[The gift begins from the moment
he thinks about Mr. Choo]

1064
00:37:54,710 --> 00:37:57,040
the whole process is part of the gift.

1065
00:37:57,830 --> 00:38:00,730
[Dex: Chu Sunghoon will probably
drink this without restraint.]

1066
00:38:01,530 --> 00:38:03,440
[Putting together the puzzle endlessly...]

1067
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:05,090
How time-consuming.

1068
00:38:05,090 --> 00:38:07,890
[1 hour and 40 minutes have passed]

1069
00:38:08,350 --> 00:38:08,650
No skin, no skin.

1070
00:38:08,650 --> 00:38:10,590
[Trembling] [No skin...]

1071
00:38:11,650 --> 00:38:17,320
[Fox's beard... and fragments of his skin...]

1072
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:20,300
[Looks like it's done little by little...]

1073
00:38:20,730 --> 00:38:22,630
[Is it the right hand?]

1074
00:38:22,790 --> 00:38:22,950
This should be right.

1075
00:38:22,950 --> 00:38:26,930
[He has to recognize this before
the left hand appears]

1076
00:38:27,290 --> 00:38:28,820
[OK!]

1077
00:38:28,820 --> 00:38:30,740
[Finally found the answer?]

1078
00:38:30,740 --> 00:38:32,610
[Shall we go eat?]

1079
00:38:34,120 --> 00:38:34,330
Seriously.

1080
00:38:34,330 --> 00:38:35,250
[I don't know. Let's go eat first.]

1081
00:38:35,250 --> 00:38:37,210
Let's go eat.

1082
00:38:37,970 --> 00:38:40,400
[Where am I? Who is he?]

1083
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:42,470
Always a dandelion.

1084
00:38:42,690 --> 00:38:42,860
But it's not good to just
gift her a book.

1085
00:38:42,860 --> 00:38:44,390
[Always Noh Hongchul]

1086
00:38:44,780 --> 00:38:44,790
What else should I give her?

1087
00:38:44,790 --> 00:38:46,890
[He wants to do more for his Manito's heart]

1088
00:38:46,890 --> 00:38:48,340
Hold on.

1089
00:38:49,050 --> 00:38:51,830
[Looking for additional gifts for Sooji]

1090
00:38:52,820 --> 00:38:55,950
[Hongchul's winter collection,
which he bought on a trip]

1091
00:38:56,550 --> 00:38:58,600
[Noh Hongchul:
Should I give her a warm Knitwear?]

1092
00:38:59,080 --> 00:39:01,710
[Wait. What color suits Sooji?]

1093
00:39:01,710 --> 00:39:02,480
Does blue or grey suit Sooji more?

1094
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:05,780
[Even carefully considering the color]

1095
00:39:05,780 --> 00:39:06,160
Blue 2, blue 3.

1096
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:06,850
[Blue 2 votes]

1097
00:39:06,850 --> 00:39:07,840
[Blue 3 votes]

1098
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:07,920
[Overwhelming votes for blue]

1099
00:39:07,920 --> 00:39:09,450
Blue.

1100
00:39:09,950 --> 00:39:10,460
Then...

1101
00:39:10,460 --> 00:39:12,720
[Satisfied] [This color will look good on her.]

1102
00:39:13,130 --> 00:39:13,220
[Decides to choose a bright blue knitwear]

1103
00:39:13,220 --> 00:39:14,940
Sooji so cute.

1104
00:39:16,170 --> 00:39:17,870
[Okay, I'm leaving!]

1105
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:18,820
[Sticks sticker!]

1106
00:39:18,820 --> 00:39:19,490
To Sooji.

1107
00:39:19,970 --> 00:39:21,300
Let's go.

1108
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:24,240
The Raccoon Dog is right here.

1109
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:26,750
[Your Manito is here right now.]

1110
00:39:28,530 --> 00:39:30,390
[It's quite far...?]

1111
00:39:30,550 --> 00:39:30,810
Let's go.

1112
00:39:30,810 --> 00:39:33,310
[It's really far, so let's get going...!]

1113
00:39:33,310 --> 00:39:33,860
It ended unexpectedly fast.

1114
00:39:33,860 --> 00:39:36,480
[Sooji, wait for me]

1115
00:39:36,770 --> 00:39:36,880
What’s going on?

1116
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:38,310
[On the other hand]
[Sooji returns to the office for secrecy]

1117
00:39:38,310 --> 00:39:39,710
OK.

1118
00:39:39,870 --> 00:39:41,220
I need to go.

1119
00:39:41,550 --> 00:39:43,630
[In a hurry]
[Jennie is in Hannam-dong right now.]

1120
00:39:43,930 --> 00:39:44,000
[Does anyone have fur?]
[Disguising herself so as not be spotted]

1121
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:45,200
Who has glasses?

1122
00:39:45,340 --> 00:39:46,160
I do.

1123
00:39:46,270 --> 00:39:47,830
Who has fur? Beard?

1124
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:49,250
[Very good!]

1125
00:39:49,250 --> 00:39:50,290
[Give it to me!]

1126
00:39:50,660 --> 00:39:50,730
[She really took out the fur...?]

1127
00:39:50,730 --> 00:39:52,160
OK.

1128
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:54,260
[No one can recognize me this way!]

1129
00:39:54,770 --> 00:39:55,480
[Give it to me!]
[Answer: Whitebeard Lee Sooji]

1130
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:56,270
Not bad.

1131
00:39:59,230 --> 00:39:59,630
It's very precious.

1132
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:00,150
[Open]

1133
00:40:00,150 --> 00:40:01,110
[Can't recognize me, can you?]

1134
00:40:01,110 --> 00:40:01,930
It's very precious.

1135
00:40:01,930 --> 00:40:04,960
[Answer: Lee Sooji holding a fan]

1136
00:40:05,240 --> 00:40:06,840
[(Manager:) I'm so nervous.]

1137
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,320
[(Manager:) I'm really nervous.]

1138
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:09,130
No way. Who can recognize me like this?

1139
00:40:09,130 --> 00:40:10,520
[Cannot understand]

1140
00:40:10,790 --> 00:40:10,800
[+props]

1141
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:12,570
Will anyone recognize me?

1142
00:40:12,700 --> 00:40:13,750
[Answer: Lee Sooji wearing a helmet.]

1143
00:40:13,750 --> 00:40:15,880
I think you'll be recognized right away.

1144
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:17,790
[(Manager:) Walk outside for 5 minutes.]

1145
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:19,010
Let’s see if people recognize you.

1146
00:40:19,010 --> 00:40:19,110
[Proposing a popularity test]

1147
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:20,110
Let's test it out.

1148
00:40:20,160 --> 00:40:21,550
Rehearsal. Rehearsal.

1149
00:40:22,330 --> 00:40:26,870
[Lee Sooji: I'll say hi
to the office guys first.]

1150
00:40:27,610 --> 00:40:29,420
[Who am I?]

1151
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:31,450
[Oh? Lee Sooji?]

1152
00:40:31,770 --> 00:40:33,270
[Immediately recognized]

1153
00:40:33,270 --> 00:40:35,060
Thank you.

1154
00:40:37,430 --> 00:40:38,430
[Oh?]

1155
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:38,720
Wait.

1156
00:40:38,720 --> 00:40:40,360
[Hello, Sooji]

1157
00:40:40,370 --> 00:40:40,690
Wait, wait.

1158
00:40:40,690 --> 00:40:43,820
[Exhausted]

1159
00:40:43,820 --> 00:40:44,740
Who am I?

1160
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:46,420
[Oh no...]

1161
00:40:46,610 --> 00:40:47,940
[Everyone knows...]

1162
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:50,260
[Sooji.]

1163
00:40:50,610 --> 00:40:53,010
[Oh, Merry Christmas.]

1164
00:40:53,430 --> 00:40:55,460
[Happy... Happy New Year.]

1165
00:40:55,860 --> 00:40:57,060
[You're so beautiful.]

1166
00:40:57,740 --> 00:41:00,760
[Thank... you.]

1167
00:41:05,310 --> 00:41:06,660
[Are you Psy?]

1168
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,840
[I'm not Psy. I'm Lee Sooji...]

1169
00:41:09,220 --> 00:41:11,250
[He really can't recognize...]

1170
00:41:11,620 --> 00:41:15,350
[This level of disguise won't work…]

1171
00:41:15,690 --> 00:41:16,790
[First…]

1172
00:41:16,790 --> 00:41:20,710
[-Manager: We still have a Santa suit!
-Forget the disguise.
I'll just wear a hat and sunglasses.]

1173
00:41:20,930 --> 00:41:22,330
[Listening.]
[Manager: We have other props.]

1174
00:41:22,330 --> 00:41:24,290
A Santa suit sounds good.

1175
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:25,970
[On YouTube: Sooji transforms into Mariah Carey]
[Source: Lee Sooji socials]

1176
00:41:25,970 --> 00:41:27,630
[The Santa suit she used back then.]
[Source: Lee Sooji socials]

1177
00:41:27,630 --> 00:41:27,920
Right. Casual clothes with a beard—

1178
00:41:27,920 --> 00:41:28,990
[Yeah, the problem is the outfit!]

1179
00:41:28,990 --> 00:41:31,010
People will think it's weird, right?

1180
00:41:31,010 --> 00:41:31,140
But if I walk around in a Santa suit,

1181
00:41:31,140 --> 00:41:32,670
[If I walk around in a Santa suit...]

1182
00:41:32,670 --> 00:41:32,880
people will think I'm doing a promo.

1183
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:35,460
[(Santa suit delivered)]

1184
00:41:35,640 --> 00:41:35,660
[Transforming into Santa!]

1185
00:41:35,660 --> 00:41:36,770
Alright.

1186
00:41:37,020 --> 00:41:38,120
Alright, alright.

1187
00:41:38,650 --> 00:41:39,740
[Who could recognize me like this?]

1188
00:41:39,740 --> 00:41:40,440
Right?

1189
00:41:40,790 --> 00:41:44,280
[Brilliant idea: slick the hair back—
no one knows if it's a man or a woman.]

1190
00:41:44,460 --> 00:41:44,570
-You really look like Psy now. -Really.

1191
00:41:44,570 --> 00:41:46,160
[Oh, you really look like Psy.]

1192
00:41:48,090 --> 00:41:48,210
[Put on sunglasses—complete!]

1193
00:41:48,210 --> 00:41:50,280
I look trendy now.

1194
00:41:50,640 --> 00:41:51,440
It's perfect.

1195
00:41:51,580 --> 00:41:52,050
Guys, you should've given me this earlier.

1196
00:41:52,050 --> 00:41:54,700
[Utterly confident
in her perfect cover-up]

1197
00:41:54,700 --> 00:41:55,950
Okay. Okay.

1198
00:41:56,090 --> 00:41:57,600
[Nobody will recognize me, right?]

1199
00:41:57,600 --> 00:41:58,020
I'm going.

1200
00:41:58,020 --> 00:41:58,520
[Lee Sooji Forever]

1201
00:41:58,520 --> 00:42:00,620
I'm going to deliver it to Jennie.

1202
00:42:06,150 --> 00:42:08,020
[Oh no, I can't find the car...]

1203
00:42:08,300 --> 00:42:08,950
[No riding Rudolf today.
I'm taking a taxi instead.]

1204
00:42:08,950 --> 00:42:10,520
What should I do?

1205
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:14,210
[Hey, kid, come here.]

1206
00:42:14,940 --> 00:42:16,400
[Did you do good deeds today? No?]

1207
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:17,790
-No. -No?

1208
00:42:17,790 --> 00:42:18,140
[A kid spotting Santa approaching]

1209
00:42:18,140 --> 00:42:20,580
Okay. Do you want to sit here?

1210
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:23,620
[-Are you back from school? -Yes.]

1211
00:42:23,620 --> 00:42:24,420
Really?

1212
00:42:24,740 --> 00:42:27,760
[Tell me what good deeds
you did this year.]

1213
00:42:28,020 --> 00:42:31,360
[Uh… I listened to Mom…]

1214
00:42:31,530 --> 00:42:33,070
[Only a part…]

1215
00:42:33,070 --> 00:42:33,280
So you only listened to part of what Mom said?

1216
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:35,340
[An honest kid]

1217
00:42:35,340 --> 00:42:35,600
Hold on.

1218
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:36,810
[Rummaging]

1219
00:42:36,810 --> 00:42:38,150
Grandpa here...

1220
00:42:38,400 --> 00:42:40,820
[I've got a gift for you.]

1221
00:42:41,610 --> 00:42:42,980
[This...]

1222
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:45,940
[-How about using it as a bookmark?
-What? ]

1223
00:42:45,940 --> 00:42:47,690
-What? -A bookmark.

1224
00:42:47,690 --> 00:42:49,170
[What's a bookmark?]

1225
00:42:49,170 --> 00:42:50,590
It's something you put in a book to mark the page.

1226
00:42:50,590 --> 00:42:54,270
[Unfortunately, it's an unwanted supply…]

1227
00:42:55,310 --> 00:42:57,070
[You don't like it?]

1228
00:42:57,370 --> 00:42:59,110
[What do you want then?]

1229
00:42:59,210 --> 00:42:59,410
What do you want then?

1230
00:42:59,410 --> 00:43:01,270
[Startled by the sudden real voice]

1231
00:43:01,540 --> 00:43:02,010
[Oh my...]

1232
00:43:02,010 --> 00:43:02,870
You...

1233
00:43:03,190 --> 00:43:06,010
[What... hahaha... do you want?]

1234
00:43:08,450 --> 00:43:10,550
[Lively.][Sorry, I don't have
anything for you…]

1235
00:43:10,550 --> 00:43:12,380
[Big-hearted][Not a single thing, really…]

1236
00:43:13,170 --> 00:43:13,410
-Where are you going? -What?

1237
00:43:13,410 --> 00:43:15,570
[Where are you going?]

1238
00:43:15,780 --> 00:43:18,670
[I... Where...]

1239
00:43:18,870 --> 00:43:20,420
[I'm... not going anywhere.]

1240
00:43:20,600 --> 00:43:22,850
[Why are you here, kid?]

1241
00:43:23,020 --> 00:43:25,660
[Because... inside...]

1242
00:43:25,850 --> 00:43:29,150
[-My family is inside. -Ah, restaurant?]

1243
00:43:29,450 --> 00:43:30,990
[-Eating? -No?]

1244
00:43:30,990 --> 00:43:32,770
-No. -What are they doing?

1245
00:43:33,080 --> 00:43:34,400
[-Is the restaurant your home? -No? ]

1246
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:36,050
-No. -Then what?

1247
00:43:36,240 --> 00:43:37,150
[It's a shop!]

1248
00:43:37,150 --> 00:43:37,510
-So it's your family's shop? -Yes.

1249
00:43:37,510 --> 00:43:39,570
[Curiosity-baiting conversation]

1250
00:43:39,830 --> 00:43:41,420
[Hey, you punk!]

1251
00:43:41,650 --> 00:43:43,580
[What, you gonna inherit the business?]

1252
00:43:43,870 --> 00:43:45,040
[Isn't this place a gourmet restaurant?]

1253
00:43:45,040 --> 00:43:46,550
[This place is packed!]

1254
00:43:46,820 --> 00:43:49,110
[-Then it'll be your shop, right? -Yes!]

1255
00:43:49,110 --> 00:43:50,590
-Yes. -You're so lucky!

1256
00:43:50,590 --> 00:43:50,760
[A kid born with gifts!]

1257
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:52,330
That place is also my family’s shop.

1258
00:43:52,330 --> 00:43:54,540
Whoa, kid.

1259
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:57,310
[Dad works here, Grandpa works there.]

1260
00:43:57,550 --> 00:44:00,680
[What? Then you give me something!]

1261
00:44:00,680 --> 00:44:00,940
Didn't I already give you this?

1262
00:44:00,940 --> 00:44:02,340
[Santa turning the tables]

1263
00:44:02,610 --> 00:44:03,020
[Searching]

1264
00:44:03,020 --> 00:44:03,740
-I don't have any. -You didn't?

1265
00:44:03,740 --> 00:44:04,920
[I don't have any?]

1266
00:44:05,150 --> 00:44:05,600
[Innocence: A precious gift.]

1267
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:07,350
